---
title: Pork and Noodle Soup Bowls with Kale and Ginger
description: This is not your ordinary noodle soup: thanks to ground pork, bites of kale, and bouncy yakisoba noodles, it’s as hale, hearty, and satisfying as can be. And with the addition of garlic, ginger, and our flavorful broth, you’ve got tons of aromatics and deep savory notes, too. We recommend hovering over the bowl, inhaling all that amazingness, and then slurping up those noodles like no one’s watching.
image: https://img.hellofresh.com/f_auto,fl_lossy,h_640,q_auto,w_1200/hellofresh_s3/image/pork-and-noodle-soup-bowls-051cc0ad.jpg
pdf: https://www.hellofresh.com/recipecards/card/pork-and-noodle-soup-bowls-5a296b59ad1d6c2b2f2bbd62-6006e819.pdf
source: https://www.hellofresh.com/recipes/pork-and-noodle-soup-bowls-5a296b59ad1d6c2b2f2bbd62
author: Sara Heilman
servings: 2
cuisine: North America
course: main course
time required: 30 minutes
nutrition:
  calories: 660 kcal
  fat: 26 g
  saturated fat: 7 g
  carbohydrates: 70 g
  sugar: 6 g
  protein: 38 g
  fiber: 4 g
  sodium: 1410 mg
---

Wash and dry all produce. Bring a #medium pot{} of salted water to a boil. Peel
@ginger{1%thumb}, then mince until you have 1 1/2 TBSP. Mince @garlic{2%clove}.
Halve, peel, and thinly slice @red onion{4%ounce}. Remove and discard stems and
large ribs from @kale{1%unit}. Roughly chop leaves. Finely mince @chili pepper{1%unit},
removing ribs and seeds first for less heat.

> If you like more heat, add more chili to taste.

Heat a drizzle of @vegetable oil{1%tsp} in a #large pot{} over medium heat. Add
onion and cook, tossing, until lightly softened, ~{2-3%minutes}. Toss in garlic,
ginger, and as much chili as you like (start with a pinch and go up from there).
Cook until fragrant, about ~{30%seconds}.

Add @ground pork{10%ounce} to pot with onion, breaking up meat into pieces.
Cook, tossing, until browned, ~{5-6%minutes}. Season with @salt{} and
@pepper{}.

Once water is boiling, add half the @yakisoba noodles{8%ounce} to pot (use the
rest as you like). Cook, stirring occasionally, until al dente, ~{2-3%minutes}.
Drain.

> If the noodles are stuck together, carefully pull them apart with your hands
> first.

Once pork in pot is browned, pour @water{4%cups} and @pho stock concentrate{2}
into same pot. Add kale and @soy sauce{2%tablespoon}, then stir to combine.
Bring to a simmer and let bubble until kale is tender, about ~{5%minutes}.

Stir drained noodles into soup in pot. Divide soup mixture between #bowls{} and
serve.